<HEADLINE>
<P>
PRESCRIPTION LIMITS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 I was just informed that after Sept. 1 all Medi-Cal recipients would be 
restricted to six prescriptions per month for medicine and pharmacists fees 
would be reduced. 
</P>
<P>
 As a pharmacist providing pharmacy services to board-and-care homes for mostly 
mentally ill patients, this will be a disaster for the patients and a disaster 
for the financial state of California. 
</P>
<P>
 Medicine is the only thing that is keeping many of the patients out of 
acute-care hospitals. Restricting patients, who are unable to pay, to six 
prescriptions will force these people into overcrowded acute-care hospitals for 
which the state costs will skyrocket. How will the state pay for the increased 
expense of hospitalization? 
</P>
<P>
 SEYMORE (SY) EPSTEIN 
</P>
<P>
 Pasadena 
</P>
</TEXT>
