<HEADLINE>
<P>
WOMEN'S TENNIS; BREAKTHROUGH FOR MEDVEDEVA 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Natalia Medvedeva of the Ukraine scored her first victory in nearly three 
months, defeating Nathalie Herreman of France, 6-0, 6-2, on Monday in the first 
round of the Toshiba Tennis Classic at the La Costa Resort and Spa. 
</P>
<P>
 No. 33 Medvedeva had lost in the first round of her last four tournaments, 
including early exits at the French Open and Wimbledon.The last time Medvedeva 
won a match was in the Prague Open in May. 
</P>
<P>
 In other matches involving seeded players, Canada's Jana Nejedly upset No. 13 
Marketa Kochta of Germany, 6-3, 5-7, 6-3, and No. 12 Ann Grossman of Grove 
City, Ohio, defeated Carrie Cunningham of Livonia, Mich., 6-3, 6-1. Lisa 
Raymond of Wayne, Pa., defeated Australia's Rennae Stubbs, 7-5, 7-6 (7-3). 
</P>
<P>
 Top-ranked Steffi Graf begins play today when she faces Alexia 
Dechaume-Balleret of France. 
</P>
