<HEADLINE>
<P>
PRO FOOTBALL DAILY REPORT; RAMS; GANDY JUMPS TO NO. 2 AT LEFT TACKLE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By T.J. SIMERS 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 First-round draft choice Wayne Gandy, who has been moved from third to second 
team, will start at left tackle in Saturday's exhibition opener against the 
Green Bay Packers at Madison, Wis.  
</P>
<P>
 "He's made a move," said Jim Erkenbeck, Ram offensive line coach."It's going 
to be hard to keep Gandy out of there. This guy can play and will play. He has 
that ability to turn it up a notch, that game tempo that makes him something 
special." 
</P>
<P>
 Gandy missed the opening of training camp while completing negotiations on a 
five-year contract. He remains No. 2 behind Clarence Jones, but Bill Schultz, 
who was working as No. 2 left tackle, has moved to right guard to challenge Tom 
Newberry. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 Quarterback T.J. Rubley, who is battling Jamie Martin for the No. 3 spot, has 
been ordered by team physicians not to throw for a week to rest a sore arm. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 The knee injury to starting defensive end Fred Stokes has given veteran Gerald 
Robinson and rookie Brad Ottis an opportunity to improve their stock. 
</P>
