<TEXT>
<P>
 Dallas Cowboys running back Derrick Lassic, backup to Emmitt Smith, faces 
surgery this week for a torn knee tendon and likely will miss the entire 
season. Lassic injured the quadriceps tendon in his right knee during Sunday 
night's exhibition victory over the Minnesota Vikings. 
