<HEADLINE>
<P>
BASEBALL DAILY REPORT; ANGELS; THESE SEATS WILL BE UP FOR GRABS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Fans used to sitting in remote corners of Anaheim Stadium for Angel games will 
get a chance to see baseball from a different perspective during a three-game 
series with Seattle beginning at 7:05 tonight. 
</P>
<P>
 Tickets throughout the stadium -- including box seats on the field and club 
levels -- are being sold for $6 on a reserved, first-come, first-served basis. 
</P>
<P>
 These are officially Mariner home games but are being played in Anaheim 
because of repair work being done on the ceiling of the Kingdome. They are not 
part of the Angels' season-ticket package. 
</P>
<P>
 Parking rates will remain the same, $5. 
</P>
<P>
 Wednesday's game will also begin at 7:05, Thursday's at 5:35. 
</P>
</TEXT>
