<P>
FOR THREE GAMES, INEXPENSIVE SEATS ARE EVERYWHERE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Fans accustomed to sitting in remote corners of Anaheim Stadium for Angel 
games will get a chance to see baseball from a different perspective during a 
three-game series with Seattle beginning at 7:05 tonight. 
</P>
<P>
 Tickets throughout the stadium -- including box seats on the field and club 
levels -- are being sold for $6 on a reserved, first-come, first-served basis. 
</P>
<P>
 These are officially Mariner home games but are being played at the Big A 
because of repair work being done on the ceiling of the Kingdome. They are not 
part of the Angels' season-ticket package. 
</P>
<P>
 Parking rates will remain $5. 
</P>
<P>
 Wednesday's game also will begin at 7:05; Thursday's at 5:35. 
