U.S. OPEN SURFING FACTS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 What: U.S. Open of Surfing, fourth stop on the world championship tour. 
</P>
<P>
 When: Today through Sunday. 
</P>
<P>
 Where: South side of Huntington Beach pier. 
</P>
<P>
 Purse: $105,000 for men's competition, $25,000 for women's, $5,000 for 
longboarding and $5,000 for bodyboarding. 
</P>
<P>
 Schedule: Competition begins at 6 a.m. Tuesday through Thursday, at 7 a.m. 
Friday and Saturday and at 8 a.m. Sunday. 
</P>
<P>
 Basics: The top men and women surfers who qualified for the 1994 world tour by 
scoring near the top of either the 1993 world tour or the world qualifying 
series. 
