unveiled a reorganization plan, reflecting what experts predict will be 
explosive growth in the wireless communications and international 
telecommunications businesses.FCC Chairman Reed Hundt said two new bureaus will 
be created over the next several months: the Wireless Telecommunications Bureau 
and the International Bureau. Longtime Senate telecommunications aide Regina 
Keeney will become chief of the wireless bureau. Also to be created are an 
Office of Workplace Diversity and a Competition Division, a move drawing upon 
Hundt's desire to expand the FCC oversight to antitrust. 
