</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Accounting Firms Limit Liability: Ernst & Young, Coopers & Lybrand and Price 
Waterhouse reorganized their partnerships to give individual partners more 
protection against lawsuits, the accounting firms said.The other three Big Six 
accounting firms -- Arthur Andersen, KPMG Peat Marwick and Deloitte & Touche -- 
said they will probably follow suit within a month or so. Under a form of 
organization called a limited liability partnership, or LLP, only partners who 
are directly involved in wrongdoing would have to tap their personal assets to 
pay judgments. All of the firm's assets would also be vulnerable, but partners 
not involved in the case would have their personal assets shielded. 
</P>
