<P>
DOWNTIME: BODY WATCH; A CRASHING WAVE, A SOARING BIRD AND SONDHEIM 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The moment my bare foot touches the sand, all of my worries vanish.Waves 
crashing, sun warming, birds soaring, breezes blowing . . . the beach calms my 
soul any time of the year. Add music, especially show tunes, and I'm energized, 
creative, centered and hopeful. Make it Stephen Sondheim music, and I'm in 
heaven. -- SUSAN L. HARRIS, Manhattan Beach 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Column 
</P>
</TYPE>
</DOC>
<DOC>
