<P>
REGIONAL EARNINGS: CHEESECAKE FACTORY REPORTS PROFIT INCREASE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Cheesecake Factory Inc., a Calabasas-based chain of restaurants, reported 
a 39% increase in profit for the second quarter ended July 3. 
</P>
<P>
 The company's profit in the latest quarter was $1.87 million, compared to net 
income of $1.35 million for the same three-month period a year ago.Revenue in 
the June quarter was $20.4 million, up 18% from revenue of $17.4 million in the 
year-earlier quarter. 
</P>
<P>
 For the first six months of 1994, Cheesecake Factory posted earnings of $3.18 
million on revenue of $39.2 million, compared to net income of $2.25 million on 
revenue of $31.2 million a year earlier. 
</P>
<P>
 Revenue and profit growth was fueled by the continued expansion of the chain, 
the company said. Cheesecake Factory has nine restaurants, in Washington, D.C.; 
Bethesda, Md.; Atlanta, Ga., and California. 
</P>
