REGIONAL EARNINGS: REXHALL INDUSTRIES' PROFIT UP 71% IN SECOND QUARTER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Rexhall Industries Inc., a Santa Clarita maker of recreational vehicles, 
reported sharp profit increases for its second quarter and its first half. 
</P>
<P>
 The company earned $532,000 in the quarter ended June 30, a 71% gain from 
$311,000 in net income a year earlier. Its sales grew 57%, to $11.6 million 
from $7.39 million. 
</P>
<P>
 For the six months, Rexhall had a profit of $1.05 million, more than double 
the $448,000 in net income in the first half of 1993. Its six-month sales 
totaled $21.9 million, up 66% from $13.2 million in sales a year before. 
</P>
<P>
 Rexhall attributed the results to its expanded dealer network and growing 
sales of restyled motor homes it introduced last year. 
