<P>
REGIONAL EARNINGS: VCNB REPORTS EARNINGS OF $29,000 IN QUARTER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Ventura County National Bancorp, a multi-bank holding company based in Oxnard, 
reported earnings of $29,000 for the second quarter ended June 30, compared 
with a loss of $2.7 million for the same quarter a year ago. 
</P>
<P>
 The latest results included $791,000 in income from its Small Business 
Administration loan portfolio as a result of a change in accounting principles. 
</P>
<P>
 The bank's total assets fell 26% to $295 million on June 30, from $398 million 
in the period a year ago. Non-performing assets totaled $15.3 million at June 
30, up 2% from a year ago. Loan loss reserves stood at $9.8 million, down 7% 
from $10.5 million a year earlier. 
</P>
<P>
 For the first six months of 1994, the bank posted a loss of $85,000, compared 
with a $4.25-million loss for the same period a year ago. 
</P>
