<HEADLINE>
<P>
BRIEFCASE: TRAVEL AND TOURISM 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
Compiled by Chris Woodyard Times staff writer 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Flying Together: USAir staged an elaborate show last week at the Four Seasons 
Hotel in Newport Center for Orange County travel agents. 
</P>
<P>
 The cocktail party and buffet was intended to show off the airlines new 
arrangement with British Airways. 
</P>
<P>
 As announced in March, the two carriers will try to operate as if they were 
one airline -- in some cases sharing aircraft and being listed together in 
travel agents' computerized reservations systems. 
</P>
<P>
 So what does it mean for Orange County? 
</P>
<P>
 USAir's daily Boeing 757 flight departing John Wayne Airport at 8 p.m. for 
Pittsburgh will connect directly with a London-bound British Airways jet. 
</P>
</TEXT>
