<HEADLINE>
<P>
BRIEFCASE: TRAVEL AND TOURISM 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
Compiled by Chris Woodyard Times staff writer 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Fun, Games and Safety: Red Lion Hotel/Orange County Airport in Costa Mesa is 
trying to begin a program to attract party animals who don't want to risk 
drunken driving. 
</P>
<P>
 Every Friday and Saturday night this summer, the hotel is offering a deal to 
allow guests to be shuttled from the hotel's Club Max to the nearby upscale 
nightclubs Shark Club and Metropolis -- then back to the hotel, where they will 
have a room waiting for them. 
</P>
<P>
 For $30 a person double occupancy, guests will find food and drink specials at 
each stop and then a chance to sleep it all off. 
</P>
<P>
 The program is being aimed at couples as well as bachelor parties and 
reunions. 
</P>
<P>
 "Everyone seems to have gotten the message that drinking and driving never 
mix, but that doesn't mean they want to stay home," said Red Lion Marketing 
Director Scott D. Williams. 
</P>
</TEXT>
