<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY BRIEFLY: FIRST AMERICAN TITLE INSURANCE ACQUIRES DALLAS-FT. WORTH 
FIRM 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 First American Title Insurance Co. said Monday that it has acquired Republic 
Title of Texas Inc., a Dallas-Fort Worth title insurer that wrote $15 million 
in premiums for 1993. 
</P>
<P>
 First American did not disclose terms of the deal. The Santa Ana-based title 
company previously owned 20% of Republic, which will continue operating under 
that name. Republic has specialized in the commercial real estate market and 
will be expanded to offer title insurance services in the residential market as 
well, First American officials said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
