<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY BRIEFLY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 ICN Pharmaceuticals Inc.: Shares of ICN and two of its subsidiaries rose 
sharply Monday after the company said it expected to announce "big news" today. 
</P>
<P>
 The Costa Mesa pharmaceutical company's stock closed at $10.50, up $1.375, on 
heavy trading on the New York Stock Exchange. Two other firms in which ICN 
Pharmaceuticals owns substantial stakes also surged. 
</P>
<P>
 Shares of SPI Pharmaceuticals Inc. shot up $2.125 to close at $21 per share. 
Meanwhile, Viratek Inc. was up $1 to finish at $10.75. A third subsidiary, ICN 
Biomedicals Inc., closed at $3.50, up 18.75 cents. 
</P>
<P>
 ICN Pharmaceuticals did not elaborate on its expected announcement, and 
officials were not immediately available for comment about Monday's stock 
gains. 
