<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: ANAHEIM; 63 ARRESTED IN VICE, NARCOTICS SWEEP 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MARTIN MILLER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A two-day police sweep near Beach Boulevard and Lincoln Avenue over the 
weekend resulted in 63 arrests for suspected vice- and narcotics-related 
crimes, police said. 
</P>
<P>
 Forty-five men were arrested Friday and Saturday on suspicion of soliciting 
prostitution by undercover female officers.Police impounded the vehicles of 
suspects who had been driving during the incidents. 
</P>
<P>
 Nine women were arrested on suspicion of solicitation of prostitution. 
</P>
<P>
 Arrests also were made on suspicion of selling narcotics, driving under the 
influence, public drunkenness and driving without a license. 
</P>
<P>
 Police launched the sweep because of continuing community complaints about 
prostitution in the neighborhood. 
</P>
<P>
 The two-day task force that conducted the operation was composed of vice 
officers, a community policing team, reserve officers and members of the Police 
Explorers. MARTIN MILLER 
</P>
