ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: SOUTH COUNTY; CHAMBER TO HOLD TRADITIONAL TARDEADA  
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The South Orange County Chamber of Commerce will hold a tardeada, a 
traditional afternoon celebration, on Aug. 27 for legislators and other elected 
officials to meet the business community. 
</P>
<P>
 The chamber's political action committee will sponsor the event, which allows 
local business people to discuss their concerns with their elected officials in 
an informal setting. 
</P>
<P>
 The tardeada will be held at Rancho Mission Viejo and is open to all business 
people in South County. The event will be from 1 to 4 p.m. and will feature a 
barbecue, clowns, magicians, music and dancing. 
</P>
<P>
 Tickets are $45 for adults and $5 for children under 12. 
</P>
<P>
 For more information, call the chamber at (714) 837-3000. 
