<TEXT>
<P>
 A memorial service will be held today for Christopher Schneider, the 
12-year-old boy who was hit by a car and killed last week. 
</P>
<P>
 The memorial service will be at 6 p.m. at the Coon and Stricklin Mortuary, 
1017 Obispo Ave., in Long Beach.A public viewing will be from 2 to 6 p.m. at 
the funeral home. 
</P>
<P>
 Christopher was waiting to walk his bike across Seal Beach Boulevard to 
McGaugh Elementary School last Tuesday afternoon when a car jumped the curb and 
hit him. 
</P>
<P>
 Police said Cynthia Kaye Lietz, 28, of Seal Beach faces various felony 
charges, including reckless driving and driving on a suspended license. 
</P>
<P>
 Police are awaiting the results of tests that will determine whether she was 
under the influence of drugs or alcohol. 
</P>
<P>
 The accident came as a shock to Seal Beach residents, who set up a shrine of 
flowers, pictures and candles at Bolsa Avenue and Seal Beach Boulevard. 
</P>
<P>
 A community meeting regarding the accident will take place Friday at 7:30 p.m. 
at the Mary Wilson Library. SHELBY GRAD 
