<BYLINE>
<P>
By JON NALICK, SPECIAL TO THE TIMES 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Intermediate schools on a year-round schedule will have back-to-school nights 
starting on Thursday, and parents are encouraged to attend with their children, 
a school district spokeswoman said Monday. 
</P>
<P>
 During the programs, parents will accompany their children on a walk-through 
of their classes.During each 15-minute class, teachers will explain lessons, 
grading and what is expected of students. Principals will also talk to parents 
about school rules, events and students' rights and responsibilities, district 
spokeswoman Diane Thomas said. 
</P>
<P>
 Intermediate schools holding back-to-school night on Aug. 4 include Carr, 
Lathrop and Spurgeon. 
</P>
<P>
 At Carr, 2120 W. Edinger Ave., the program will begin at 5:30 p.m. 
</P>
<P>
 At Lathrop, 1111 S. Broadway, the program will begin at 7 p.m. 
</P>
<P>
 At Spurgeon, 2701 W. 5th St., the program will begin at 6:30 p.m. 
</P>
<P>
 Sierra Intermediate will have its back-to-school night at 6:30 p.m. Aug. 11. 
The campus is at 1901 N. McClay St. 
</P>
