<HEADLINE>
<P>
EDUCATION; GOOD SCHOOLS, BARGAIN PRICES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Is more money the only way to achieve high-quality schools? An analysis of 
school districts nationwide found many are producing high-achieving students at 
low cost. The study by American Demographics magazine found that student 
performance in other districts lags despite generous school budgets. 
Dollars-and-cents analyses of school performance are rising as employers raise 
doubts about the quality of graduates and taxpayers wonder if money is being 
handled wisely. The Brain Belt 
