<P>
WEST VENTURA COUNTY FOCUS: SEACLIFF; STATION WAGON SPLIT IN HALF IN ACCIDENT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By PHYLLIS W. JORDAN 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A station wagon hit a Ventura Freeway guard rail near Seacliff and was sheared 
in two early Monday morning, leaving a passenger with back injuries and cuts. 
</P>
<P>
 Esther Lee, 24, of British Columbia, remained in fair condition at Ventura 
County Medical Center after the accident that police said occurred when the 
driver fell asleep at the wheel. 
</P>
<P>
 Lee and Jin Kang, 20, of Riverside were traveling south on the Ventura Freeway 
on a nonstop trip from Seattle, according to California Highway Patrol reports. 
Kang, driving about 65 m.p.h., nodded off at the wheel, and the 1989 Mercury 
Tracer began veering toward the guardrail, police said. 
</P>
<P>
 Kang tried to turn back onto the road, but the car hit the end of the 
guardrail just behind the right front door, police said. That effectively split 
the car into two pieces, which ended up 150 feet apart after the accident. The 
crash occurred shortly after 5 a.m., about half a mile south of Seacliff. 
</P>
<P>
 Kang suffered minor injuries and was not admitted to the hospital. Lee 
suffered a fractured back, as well as lacerations to her face and back. Both 
were wearing seat belts, police said. PHYLLIS W. JORDAN 
</P>
</TEXT>
