<P>
EAST VENTURA COUNTY FOCUS: MOORPARK; TAKASUGI PLANS A 'BUSINESS WALK' 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By PHYLLIS W. JORDAN 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Assemblyman Nao Takasugi, stressing the importance of small business, will 
walk through Moorpark's Gateway Plaza on Friday to meet some of the companies 
he represents. 
</P>
<P>
 "It's important to understand that whether a business has 100 employees or 
just one, they are essential to California's economy," the Oxnard Republican 
said in a statement."As a small businessman for over 35 years, I understand 
firsthand the needs and concerns of business owners." 
</P>
<P>
 In one of his occasional "business walks" through the 37th district, Takasugi 
has scheduled at least six stops at the center on East Los Angeles Drive. 
</P>
<P>
 Typically, he uses contacts he makes on the walks for business advisory boards 
and committees. Local firms, in turn, have an opportunity to discuss the 
problems and changes the state Assembly should address. "We still have a lot of 
work to do in Sacramento for California's businesses," he said. PHYLLIS W. 
JORDAN 
</P>
