<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY EARNINGS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Tokos Medical Corp.: The Santa Ana provider of high-risk obstetrical health 
care services lost $306,000, or 2 cents a share, for the second quarter.That 
compared to a loss of $6.6 million, or 38 cents a share, for the same period a 
year earlier. The 1993 period included $6 million in restructuring charges. 
Revenue declined 15% to $26.4 million from $31.2 million. For the first half, 
the company posted a loss of $2.5 million, or 14 cents a share, compared to a 
loss of $7 million, or 40 cents a share, for the like period of 1993. Six-month 
revenue fell 22% to $51.4 million from $66.1 million. 
</P>
</TEXT>
